<item>
            <title>[DERBY-1244] ij no longer returns error messages based on derby.ui.locale</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-1244</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;ij no longer resolves derby.ui.locale after checkin of revision 395088 (for ij --help)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Before this change one could get the following:&lt;br/&gt;
-----------------&lt;br/&gt;
java -Dderby.ui.locale=de_DE org.apache.derby.tools.ij&lt;br/&gt;
IJ Version 10.2&lt;br/&gt;
ij&amp;gt; connect &apos;jdbc:derby:bladb&apos;;&lt;br/&gt;
ij&amp;gt; create table t(c1 int);&lt;br/&gt;
0 Zeilen eingef..gt/aktualisiert/gel..scht&lt;br/&gt;
ij&amp;gt; select x;&lt;br/&gt;
FEHLER 42X01: Syntax error: Encountered &quot;&amp;lt;EOF&amp;gt;&quot; at line 1, column 8.&lt;br/&gt;
ij&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
------------------&lt;br/&gt;
(I replaced the on my system funkily displayed u- and o-umlaut with .. ). &lt;br/&gt;
Now, the same process goes like this:&lt;br/&gt;
------------------&lt;br/&gt;
$ &amp;gt;java -Dderby.ui.locale=de_DE org.apache.derby.tools.ij&lt;br/&gt;
ij version 10.2&lt;br/&gt;
ij&amp;gt; connect &apos;jdbc:derby:bladb&apos;;&lt;br/&gt;
ij&amp;gt; create table t(c1 int);&lt;br/&gt;
0 rows inserted/updated/deleted&lt;br/&gt;
ij&amp;gt; select x;&lt;br/&gt;
ERROR 42X01: Syntax error: Encountered &quot;&amp;lt;EOF&amp;gt;&quot; at line 1, column 8.&lt;br/&gt;
ij&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
--------------------&lt;br/&gt;
(I&apos;m a little puzzled why even when things apparently worked ok, there is the English &apos;Syntax error&apos;, but that&apos;s another issue).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I svn-updated back until the German showed up again, and with revision 395014 all is ok, with 395088 it&apos;s wrong.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
